Package pw.ollie.politics.universe

Class Citizen

  • java.lang.Object
    • pw.ollie.politics.universe.Citizen
  • public final class Citizen
extends Object
    A Citizen is a player's representation in a single Universe in Politics.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      Set<Group> getGroups()
      Gets a Set of all Groups of the Citizen - that is, all Groups the player is part of in the Universe this Citizen is active in.
      Set<Group> getGroups​(GroupLevel level)
      Gets the Set of all Group of the specified GroupLevel the player is a member of, or an empty Set if the player is not a member of a Group of that level in this Citizen's Universe.
      String getName()
      Gets the in-game name of the player represented by this Citizen/
      UUID getUniqueId()
      Gets the unique identifier of the player represented by this Citizen.
      Universe getUniverse()
      Gets the Universe this Citizen is active within.

        public Set<Group> getGroups()
        Gets a Set of all Groups of the Citizen - that is, all Groups the player is part of in the Universe this Citizen is active in. Groups the player is part of, but which are not present in the particular universe, are not included.
        Returns:
        the player's Group's in this Citizen's particular Universe

      • getGroups

        Parameters:
        level - the GroupLevel to get the player's Groups in this Citizen's Universe of
        Returns:
